### Things you can do

If you're feeling particularly ambitious, here are some tasks awaiting the attention of someone with more time and hope than is strictly advisable.

*   **Article requests**: Apparently, these topics don't exist yet. Feel free to fill the void: Executive branch of the government of the State of Illinois, Fort Gage, History of European exploration in Illinois, Morris Selz, [Pre-Columbian history of Illinois](/Pre-Columbian_history_of_Illinois), Wayne Motley, Western Wheel Company, Citizens Utility Board. Don't all rush at once.
*   **Assess**: There are articles in [Category:Unassessed WikiProject Illinois articles](/Category:Unassessed_WikiProject_Illinois_articles) and [Category:Unknown-importance WikiProject Illinois articles](/Category:Unknown-importance_WikiProject_Illinois_articles) that need judging. Bring your gavel.
*   **Collaborate**: The current collaboration of the week for WikiProject Chicago is [Ronald Crane](/Ronald_Crane). If that name means anything to you, get to it.
*   **Copyedit**: Peruse [Category:WikiProject Illinois articles needing attention](/Category:WikiProject_Illinois_articles_needing_attention) and [Category:Illinois articles needing expert attention](/Category:Illinois_articles_needing_expert_attention) to fix the prose of others. It's easier than fixing your own life.
*   **Deletion sorting**: Visit [WikiProject Deletion sorting/Illinois](/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Deletion_sorting/Illinois) to weigh in on what deserves to be wiped from existence.
*   **Expand**: These articles are considered inadequate. Make them less so: [Government of Illinois](/Government_of_Illinois), the biographies in [List of Governors of Illinois](/List_of_Governors_of_Illinois), [Casimir Pulaski Day](/Casimir_Pulaski_Day), [Constitution of Illinois](/Constitution_of_Illinois), [Democratic Party of Illinois](/Democratic_Party_of_Illinois), [Economy of Illinois](/Economy_of_Illinois), [Flag and seal of Illinois](/Flag_and_seal_of_Illinois), ["Illinois"](/Illinois_(state_song)), [Illinois Republican Party](/Illinois_Republican_Party), [Illinois Secretary of State](/Illinois_Secretary_of_State), [Illinois state parks](/Illinois_state_parks), and the list and introduction on [List of battles fought in Illinois](/List_of_battles_fought_in_Illinois).
*   **Featured article candidates**: Someone thinks [Illinois](/Illinois) and [Springfield, Illinois](/Springfield,_Illinois) can be elevated to [Featured Article](/Wikipedia:Featured_article_criteria) status. An optimistic soul.
*   **Geographical coordinates**: There are articles in [Category:Illinois articles missing geocoordinate data](/Category:Illinois_articles_missing_geocoordinate_data). They are lost. Help them be found.
*   **Infobox**: See [Category:Illinois articles needing infoboxes](/Category:Illinois_articles_needing_infoboxes). They're naked. Clothe them with data.
*   **Maintain**: This portal, Portal:Illinois, requires upkeep. You're looking at it.
*   **Map**: People have requested maps. See [Category:Wikipedia requested maps in Illinois](/Category:Wikipedia_requested_maps_in_Illinois).
*   **Photo**: There are requests for pictures in [Category:Wikipedia requested photographs in Illinois](/Category:Wikipedia_requested_photographs_in_Illinois).
*   **Stubs**: These are barely articles. Flesh them out. See [Category:Illinois stubs](/Category:Illinois_stubs), [Category:Illinois geography stubs](/Category:Illinois_geography_stubs), [Category:Illinois politician stubs](/Category:Illinois_politician_stubs), [Category:Illinois school stubs](/Category:Illinois_school_stubs).
*   **Unreferenced**: Hunt down sources for [Unreferenced BLPs](/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Illinois/Unreferenced_BLPs) and articles in [Category:Unreferenced WikiProject Illinois articles](/Category:Unreferenced_WikiProject_Illinois_articles).
*   **Other**: Find articles that belong in [Category:Illinois](/Category:Illinois) or its subcategories and add them. Tag their talk pages with `{{`[`WikiProject Illinois`](/Template:WikiProject_Illinois)`}}`.

